The Chronicle Fungai Muderere, Senior Sports Reporter FORGOTTEN ex-Highlanders’ star Mubarike ‘Mamba’ Chisoni is on cloud nine after attaining a United States of America Soccer National A Senior Coaching Licence. The US National A License course is reportedly designed to introduce concepts targeted at coaching older players (older junior level and senior level players). <img class="size-full wp-image-526602" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/01/Soccer.jpeg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/01/Soccer.jpeg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/01/Soccer-360x200.jpeg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The A Licence focuses on recognising principles of the game and technical applications in 11 vs 11 game format and how these principles influence positional, group and team organisation.